{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959616,"pPcc":"SAT#S","questionId":"ec5d4823","skill_cd":"S.A.","score_band_range_cd":4,"skill_desc":"Area and volume","createDate":1691007959616,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Geometry and Trigonometry","ibn":"020533-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"S","uId":"1ec46cf1-e047-4c1e-815f-80da61da24c1","difficulty":"M"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"020533-DC","section":"Math","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">What is the volume, in cubic centimeters, of a right rectangular prism that has a length of 4&nbsp;centimeters, a width of 9&nbsp;centimeters, and a height of 10&nbsp;centimeters? </p>\n","answer":{"style":"SPR","rationale":"<p>The correct answer is 360. The volume of a right rectangular prism is calculated by multiplying its dimensions: length, width, and height. Multiplying the values given for these dimensions yields a volume of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 times 9, times 10, equals 360\"></span> cubic centimeters.</p>\n"}}}